description:
The body::before blueprint grid in globals.css uses background-size: 48px 48px with no background-position offset. On common viewport widths (1280/1440/1536px), a vertical grid line lands exactly at the horizontal center of the viewport — which is also the center of the centered content layout. This makes one grid line appear much more prominent than the others, looking like an unintentional vertical divider rather than a subtle texture.

Fix: add background-position: 24px 24px to the body::before rule in globals.css. This offsets the grid by half a cell, ensuring no line falls at the exact center on standard viewport widths.

  body::before {
    ...
    background-size: 48px 48px;
    background-position: 24px 24px;  /* add this */
  }

Acceptance: the blueprint grid reads as uniform texture, no single line appears more prominent than others.

---

## STEP 5 — Font and glow CSS variables (required by Arcana theme)

Add three additional CSS variables to ALL theme blocks (dark, light, terminal, arcana).
Non-arcana themes set these to passthrough/none values so Arcana-specific code is inert.

### Variables to add

```css
/* Font family variables — used by Tailwind font-display and font-body utilities */
--font-display: inherit;   /* arcana overrides: 'Cinzel', Georgia, serif */
--font-body: inherit;      /* arcana overrides: 'IM Fell English', Garamond, serif */

/* Text glow — used by .text-glow utility class */
--text-glow: none;         /* arcana overrides: 0 0 8px rgb(124 58 237 / 0.6), ... */
```

Add to `:root, [data-theme="dark"]`, `[data-theme="light"]`, `[data-theme="terminal"]`:
  --font-display: inherit;
  --font-body: inherit;
  --text-glow: none;

### Tailwind utilities to add (tailwind.config.ts or globals.css @layer utilities)

```css
@layer utilities {
  .font-display { font-family: var(--font-display); }
  .font-body    { font-family: var(--font-body); }
  .text-glow    { text-shadow: var(--text-glow); }
}
```

### Acceptance criteria additions
- [ ] `--font-display`, `--font-body`, `--text-glow` defined in all theme blocks
- [ ] `.font-display`, `.font-body`, `.text-glow` Tailwind utilities work
- [ ] Non-arcana themes: font utilities have no effect (inherit), text-glow has no effect (none)
